<div class='panel panel-default'>
  <div class="panel-heading">Search tips</div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <ul class="advanced-help">
      <li>NB: This advanced search screen <strong>only</strong> searches local content.</li>
      <li>Please use the <strong>Articles Advanced Search</strong> to search for non-local content.</li>
      <li>Select <strong>match all</strong> to require all fields.
     </li>

     <li>Select <strong>match any</strong> to find at least one field.
     </li>

     <li>Combine keywords and attributes to find specific items.
     </li>

     <li>Use <strong>quotation</strong> marks to search as a phrase. 
     
       <li>Use <strong>+</strong> before a term to make it required. (Otherwise results matching only some of your terms may be included).</li>
     
       <li>Use <strong>-</strong> before a word or phrase to exclude. 

         <li>Use <strong>OR</strong>, <strong>AND</strong>, and <strong>NOT</strong> to create complex boolean logic. You can use parentheses in your complex expressions. </li>
     <li>Truncation and wildcards are not supported - word-stemming is done automatically.</li>
   </ul>
  </div>
</div>
